rsync -arv -e "ssh -p 22999" example.com root@ipaddress:/home/username/

Go in the source path and replace the * with the folder that is required.
rsync -va -e "ssh -p 22999" *  root@ipaddress:/home/username/


Easiest is to go thr file location and then copy replace source and then go to destination.

rsync -arv -e "ssh -p 22999" <sourcefoldername> root@ipaddress:/home/username/

Here destination is root@serverIP and then the path.


example:

rsync -arv -e "ssh -p 22999" index.php root@103.212.121.73:/home/packmate/public_html
